result.execSummary:
The defendant Anthony A Logan was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Sex with Child Age 16 or Older [Modifiers: Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 948.09.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

11:58 a.m.  State by ADA Lisa Vanden Branden.  Defendant present, in custody, with Attorney Jon Wilsnack.

ADA recites agreement - amend 1 count of sexual  intercourse with child over age of 16 and as a repeater in violation of 948.09.  DRI count 2.  Attorney Wilsnack concurs.  Defendant concurs.

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - waived.  Court goes over the elements of the offense.  Court instructs regarding the maximum penalties.  Court instructs regarding deportation.  

Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST to count 1.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently, and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty of the amended charge on count 1.  Court DRI count 2.  Court orders a judgment of conviction be entered today.  

ADA confirms compliance with any victim/witness rights.  Sentencing argument by ADA.  Statement by Attorney Wilsnack.  No statement by the defendant.

Court makes statement regarding repeater as to elements and as to the maximum penalties.  

SWD, placed on probation for 24 months.
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
Complete AODA and comply with any recommended treatment.
NO contact with the victim.  Court instructs regarding forms of no contact.
Pay court costs.
Abide with all other rules/recommendations as imposed by the supervising agent. 
Court grants jail credit for 1/21/2014 if probation is revoked.
